{"questionId":"21409","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A game is played where two unbiased dice are rolled and the score in the game is the&nbsp;greater of the two numbers shown. If the two numbers are the same, then the score in the&nbsp;game is the number shown on one of the dice. A diagram showing the possible outcomes is&nbsp;given below.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/f29e27dfdfd95e6f383c459d1be41d4a81fb87a3.png\"></p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> be the random variable “the score in a game”.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the expected score of a game.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow><mn>36</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>161</mn><mn>36</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"false\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>36</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>47</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>47222</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21409","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.10c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the expected score of a game.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"mem